==Finnish==
([[Wiktionary:Finnish_index_s|index S]])
From ancient ''*tinä'' which has produced the verb person suffix ''-t''.

===Personal pronoun===
'''sinä''' (''stem'' '''sinu-''')
# [[you]] (''singular'', ''familiar'')

===Alternative spellings===
*[[sa]] (''archaic or poetic'')
*[[sie]] (''dialectal'')
*[[sä]] (''colloquial or dialectal'')
*[[sää]] (''dialectal'')

====Declension====
The suffixes are regular. The [[abessive]], [[comitative]] and [[instructive]] forms don't exist.

